<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>1992-07-31</DATELINE><TITLE>Myelitis and Meningitis</TITLE><BODY>The inflammatory diseases most commonly affecting the spinal cord meninges and parenchyma of dogs and cats are discussed. Clinical signs, lesion localization, differential diagnoses, diagnostic procedures, therapeutic regimens, and prognosis are described.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>